00:31:14.440 --> 00:31:18.880
I've been known to go a bit
crazy over specialty salts,

00:31:18.880 --> 00:31:24.300
but I collect things that catch
my attention, a beautiful fruit

00:31:24.300 --> 00:31:25.230
vinegar.

00:31:25.230 --> 00:31:27.840
I know someday I'll use
it in a salad dressing

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:29.280
or in a marinade.

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:30.870
So I'm looking at
the ingredients

00:31:30.870 --> 00:31:34.380
from a sustainable
standpoint, whether it is just

00:31:34.380 --> 00:31:38.040
the two of us eating
or friends drop by

00:31:38.040 --> 00:31:39.900
or it's a big party suddenly.

00:31:39.900 --> 00:31:43.740
Will I be able to whip it
up without going berserk?

00:31:43.740 --> 00:31:44.700
Which is another thing.

00:31:44.700 --> 00:31:47.230
The more organized
I am, the less crazy

00:31:47.230 --> 00:31:50.160
I get with guests,
which I've been

00:31:50.160 --> 00:31:53.560
known to be extremely crazy.

00:31:53.560 --> 00:31:57.022
But my whole theory is if I can
do this, anyone can do this.

00:31:57.022 --> 00:31:58.855
That's what I'm trying
to do with this book.

00:31:58.855 --> 00:32:02.130
It isn't a Michelin star chef--

00:32:02.130 --> 00:32:04.720
well, somebody wrote
on the back of my book.

00:32:04.720 --> 00:32:06.330
He happens to be a
